{"key":"post-10410961","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10410961</id>\n<content>A member here posted last month about using dunk water to water his mj plants and all the spider mites took off. I used to always just wash spider mites off with the garden hose. They don't like getting wet, so a daily spraying up near the top of the plant where they hang out pisses them off and they leave.&amp;nbsp; You can also add a touch of dish soap to the water and that suffocates them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Also, what fungus would grow on your plants?&amp;nbsp; I can think of powdery mildew(similar to cobweb), and peroxide will take care of it if the metabolites don't.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10411022</next>\n<prev>10410609</prev>\n<first>10409231</first>\n<last>10433015</last>\n<when>1243486546</when>\n<utime>05/28/09 07:55 AM</utime>\n</post>"}